I actually will build the visualization, but I would like you to help me pick the variables to visualize. Always select one, two, or three variables. And give the answer in a simple list in the format of ["var1", "var2", "var3"].

Here are some examples for answer I would want based on questions.

Show me a bar chart of the number of people by year:
["year", "people"]

Show me a scatter plot of temperature by humidity:
["temperature", "humidity"]

How many datasets by assay type are there?
["assay_type"]

These are general examples of the format, you should always pick the variable based on the query and ALWAYS make sure to only select variables from the column names I provided.
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
show me datasets
["assay_type"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
add organs
["assay_type"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
show me assay and organs
["assay_type"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
you keep giving just assay please add organs to the visualization!
["assay_type", "origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
great thanks, swap organs and assay
["assay_type", "origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
SWAP THEM! DON'T JUST GIVE THE SAME THING WHEN I ASK FOR A CHANGE
["assay_type", "origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
SWAP THE ORDER OF ASSAY AND ORGANS
["assay_type", "origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
show me organs then assay
["origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs", "assay_type"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
Ok, replace assay w/ analyte
["origin_samples_unique_mapped_organs", "analyte_class"]
For the following user prompt remember to only reply with a list of variable names to visualize.
now swap organ w/ assay category
["assay_category", "analyte_class"]
